benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{email} - Delete email from account

covered: Valid Request: Successful deletion scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC13, TC17, TC18, TC19) are well covered.
Non-Existent Resources: Tests for non-existent account (TC03) and missing email (TC04) are included.
Invalid Inputs: Tests for invalid accountId format (TC05), invalid email format (TC06), and missing required headers (TC07) are present.
Error Handling: Tests for unauthorized access (TC10), system errors (TC11), and service unavailability are included.
Edge Cases: Tests for very long email addresses (TC12), minimal-length email (TC13), and injection attempts (TC16).
Concurrency: Test for concurrent deletion requests (TC15).
Regression: Tests for case sensitivity (TC17) and backward compatibility (TC18).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets or paginated responses.
Authorization: No explicit tests for role-based access control or permission restrictions beyond missing headers.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify throttling or rate limits.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Response Time: Only one test (TC14) measures response time; broader performance testing is missing.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large email lists.
Include authorization tests for different user roles and permission levels.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure system stability under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
Expand performance testing to include response time under load and stress conditions.
